title: fake notifications
extract: A fake DHL email containing malware is putting Australian inboxes at risk. ... While the sender appears to be 'DHL- Services Notification', the email has been sent from a compromised mailbox. The attachment, is an '.exe' or executable file – meaning it has the ability to automatically run a task.Jan 20, 2017
